      • isPropertyWithMultipleValuesEqual

        default boolean isPropertyWithMultipleValuesEqual(WapObject wapObject2,
                                                  org.apache.commons.rdf.api.IRI propertyName)
        Compare if the values for the given WapObject of a given property are equal to ours.
        They are equal if we have the same amount of values for the property and we contain the same values, not depending on order.
        Parameters:
        wapObject2 - The second annotation
        propertyName - The property to check
        Returns:
        true, if is property with multiple values equal

      • isPropertyEqual

        default boolean isPropertyEqual(WapObject wapObject2,
                                org.apache.commons.rdf.api.IRI propertyName)
        Compare if the value for a given given WapObject of a given property is equal to ours.
        It is equal if we both don't have it, or if we both have it and the two are equal.

        If it is not guaranteed that only one value of the given property may exist, use isPropertyWithMultipleValuesEqual(WapObject, IRI) instead.

        Parameters:
        wapObject2 - The second WapObject
        propertyName - The property to check
        Returns:
        true if equals, false otherwise
